Complete Implementation Plan
Architecture Decisions (Confirmed)
Decision	Choice
Admin login	Separate /admin/login page
Purchase unit	Credits/Slots (Option B)
Billing cycle	Monthly subscription ₹499/user
On expiry	7-day grace period → account locked
Data on lock	Preserved, never deleted
Payment flow	Fake simulated gateway (Razorpay-style)
Admin dashboard	New enterprise-style dashboard
User creation	Superadmin creates → user completes on first login
Phase 1: Separate Admin Authentication
New /admin/login route and template
Superadmin sessions completely separate from user sessions
Regular /login blocks superadmin accounts from logging in
/admin/* routes all protected by admin session, not Flask-Login user session
Phase 2: New Admin Dashboard
/admin/dashboard — metrics: credits remaining, active users, grace period users, monthly spend
/admin/users — user list with status (active, grace, locked), create user button
/admin/billing — credit wallet, transaction history, buy more credits button
Clean sidebar navigation, enterprise UI
Phase 3: Credit/Wallet System
Firestore collections needed:


credits/
  {superadmin_id}/
    balance: 10          # available slots
    total_purchased: 20
    last_updated: ...

transactions/
  {id}/
    type: 'purchase'|'deduction'|'refund'
    amount: 4990         # in rupees
    credits: 10
    user_id: ...         # if deduction, which user
    created_at: ...
    payment_id: ...      # fake payment reference
Phase 4: Fake Payment Gateway
/admin/billing/checkout?credits=10 — order summary page
/admin/billing/payment — fake Razorpay-style UI (card fields, pay button)
2 second loading spinner → success page
Credits added to wallet on success
Transaction record created
Phase 5: User Management with Credits
Create user form: name, email, temp password, role, department
On create → check if credits > 0 → deduct 1 credit → create user
User gets must_change_password: true, is_active: true, subscription_status: 'active'
If no credits → block creation with "Insufficient credits, please purchase more"
Phase 6: Subscription Lifecycle
New fields on user document:


must_change_password: true
subscription_status: 'active'|'grace'|'locked'
subscription_start: date
subscription_expires: date      # start + 30 days
grace_period_ends: date         # expires + 7 days
Monthly job logic (can be a manual trigger for now):

Check all users where subscription_expires < today
Move to grace status → superadmin sees warning banner
After grace_period_ends < today → move to locked
Phase 7: First Login Flow
After login, check must_change_password
If true → redirect to /change-password (cannot skip)
User sets new password + completes profile (phone, profile picture optional)
Sets must_change_password: false
Redirected to main app
Phase 8: Login Gate
Regular /login → checks subscription_status
active or grace → allow login (grace shows banner)
locked → block with "Your account is inactive, contact your administrator"
/admin/login → only is_superadmin: true accounts, no subscription check
Build Order

1. Admin login (separate session)
2. Admin dashboard shell (UI)
3. Credit wallet + Firestore collections
4. Fake payment gateway
5. User creation with credit deduction
6. Subscription status fields + login gate
7. First login / forced password change
8. Grace period warnings + locked state
This gives us a production-ready architecture that can swap the fake gateway for real Razorpay with minimal changes.

